Articles.Content:
7 hours ago, Baladain said:

Running KSP 1.4.5 and IFS 1.4.5

fuel switching is not working for me on stock tanks.

FSfuelswitch does not even show in the part descriptions.

I was just about to post the same thing. It was working in the last version (as far as I recall). When I installed the new version after the recent KSP update I can no longer fill stock tanks with just LF/LOX/LF+LOX. It only has the option to change the size of the tank.

I hope this can be resolved as I rely on having a full LF tank on some of my craft (some already in flight).

Cheers!

I was just about to post the same thing. It was working in the last version (as far as I recall). When I installed the new version after the recent KSP update I can no longer fill stock tanks with just LF/LOX/LF+LOX. It only has the option to change the size of the tank.

I had to roll back to version 3.6.1 from here

https://kerbal.curseforge.com/projects/interstellar-fuel-switch/files

2 hours ago, Baladain said:

I had to roll back to version 3.6.1 from here

https://kerbal.curseforge.com/projects/interstellar-fuel-switch/files

Thanks, that works fine. I'll stick with this version for now.

Cheers

Small bug to report - on many if not all stock tanks where IFS allows for switching to xenon, resource amounts end up being 1 xenon per 1 unit of LF/OX volume in the tank originally. This is off by a factor of ~18-57 (depending on which stock parts we're supposed to take as models). For example: in the FLT100 (100 LF/OX volume), switching to xenon results in a tank that holds 100 xenon. It should hold about 5700 xenon going by the stock PB-750 (or whatever it's called).

My guess is that somewhere in the patches, the Xenon resource value was set to 1 * the original LF/OX volume...
